13: Is this really the best you can do?
15:
You're weak... Weak from all those
pesky emotions. You'll never be able
to beat me.
18:
Stand up, dog. I'll carve out this
lesson into your flesh.
22:
...Not a patient bone in your body, is
there?
25:
Give me just a little bit longer, and
then I'll be ready.
33:
I'm very close to completing my
analysis.
38: Hmm. And now I do... this?
48:
You dare steal the techniques I
honed and made my own?
52:
You've got gutsâ€”ones that I'll rip out
of you.
57: So this is the strength of a monster.
62:
I'm not interested in testing it out
further. It's nap time, Little Lady.
65:
Honestly... A nap doesn't... sound too
bad at the moment...
70:
Who I really am? What are you
going on about, Teo?
73:
You should know better than
anyone else the rage and hatred
inside me.
76:
This world doesn't have a place for
us.
79:
Teo... Join me, and we'll make a
world where we both belong.
83:
No one will ever hurt us again. By our
own hands there will be peace.
87:
How? By forcing others to obey with
the crown?
91:
...We don't have a choice. This world
is already rotten to the core.
93:
Without tearing out its foundation
first, we can't rebuild. Don't you
understand?
97:
I don't want to live in a world like
that.
100: Not after I finally figured out...
102:
That we don't have to hurt anyone
to have a place in this world.
107: ...Just who do you think you are?
111:
I know what it's like... To feel that the
entire world is against you. But...
117:
S-silence! You DARE presume to
know everything I've been through?
You, some half-grown brat?!
120:
Crown of the Beast King! Roar
mighty and proud, and reduce all to
beasts!
132:
N-no! You were supposed to follow
my will!
136:
Why won't you work like you're
supposed to? Answer me, Goddess
of the Stars!
140:
...Sorry, but she's not taking
questions right now.
145:
Even if she were, she wouldn't be
helping you with a goal like that.
153:
My mom said that the crown could
change a species, but... She never
mentioned anything about
recreating the entire world.
159:
You can't be serious... What did I do
all this for, then?!
163:
Give it up, Magnos. Your wish was
impossible from the start!
168:
Then how! How am I supposed to
find a place to belong?!
176:
I found people who accept me for
who I am. I know you can too!
181:
D-don't be ridiculous! If people like
that truly existed, then why...
186:
I'm here, aren't I?! I accept you for
who you are.
189:
I remember how you apologized to
me when I got hurt...
197:
I mean, you've done some awful
things... But you've still got some
kindness in you.
201:
Please, don't throw it away. There's
been enough pain and suffering.
205:
...I see now that you and I are
nothing alike.
209: Because I can't change who I am.
223: Why would you go so far?
229:
If the world won't accept me for who
I am, then I'll hollow out a place in it...
with my dying breath!
233:
I'll become the monster... that the
world always saw me as!
248:
What's the plan, Teo? Should we put
him out of his misery?
263:
Then that's what we'll do. You ready,
Teo?
